    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review. Here's a quick summary:\n\n**5 files** to create/modify:\n\n1. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core implementation with `Geo` interface, `geo()`, `geoFromHeaders()`, `isInRegion()`, and `geoDistance()` (Haversine). Extracts from Vercel `x-vercel-ip-*` headers with Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` fallback, includes 10-entry `COUNTRY_NAMES` map, URL-decodes city names.\n\n2. **`packages/next/geo.js`** — Public CJS entry point following the exact `server.js` pattern (const object → `module.exports` → individual `exports.*`).\n\n3. **`packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — Type re-exports following the `server.d.ts` pattern.\n\n4. **`packages/next/package.json`** — Add `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` to `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"`.\n\n5. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — 13 Jest test cases covering all functions, edge cases, and the NY→London distance calculation.",
